Dar es Salaam Regional Commissioner Abubakar Kunenge has revealed that the city is set to allocate special business places for women, as a strategy to empower the group economically. Speaking at the commemoration of Women’s Day in Dar es Salaam on Monday, the RC revealed Tanzania's commercial capital plan which aims at empowering women who are mostly seen in street, vending various products. The regional boss was optimistic that the plan will enable to contribute to the country’s economic growth.